Special shout out to my friend jcurtis_atelier, who made this cowl for me. So talented.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/N0wa8tW</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[rectalpossum]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>and so it begins...</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/p5zTQCV</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/usexuzH.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/p5zTQCV</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[fulcrims]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I was stuck in an abusive relationship for three years. This is all that’s left of my ex.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/gv9LxgG</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/3eq0wUn.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I was physically and emotionally abused for three years, trapped by my visual impairment making it difficult to transport myself. Repeated failure of first responders and mandatory reporters to help or provide resources was used against me. Cops finally arrested my ex in March, giving me a 72 hour window of safety and resources that could help in the meantime. I was granted a temporary restraining order which was violated. I was granted a four year restraining order on the first of April. It has also been violated. I had to quit my job due to fear at home, and concerns for my safety. My ex has repeatedly tried to file civil cases against me. I had to get a victims rights lawyer. A judge has thrown them all out. There’s no anonymous address I can go to- all shelters and programs are full (that accept men). I was financially abused and left with a trashed house, a ton of debt, and unpaid utility bills. There are no programs in my state that help domestic violence victims without children with rent or utilities. Because I went on leave with my job before quitting, I can’t get unemployment. I literally lost everything. But. My ex never dealt with his stuff. I’d been cleaning and packing and realized I really didn’t have anything material. I had almost no physical possessions. What I did have, was a roof over my head for the time being, a dog, a therapist, a landlord being understanding, and my future ahead of me for the first time in a long time. I was almost done with my undergraduate in math, so I went back to school at time and a half so I can graduate in December. I focused on creating social connections locally, something that had been impossible previously. I hike with my dog every day. Behind me in this picture is the last of the physical belongings I need to sort through. My house is almost mine again. I don’t know what I’m feeling right now. I still don’t feel safe - but I feel like soon, I can have something that’s mine. Time to finish up.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/gv9LxgG</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[deilanntau]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/XOKUd1E</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/wEJigIn.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/XOKUd1E</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[mfrybeasley]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>She trusted the babysitter</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/nczkNjX</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/lGcZSm1.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>#cat#kitten#dog#cute#cute_animal#aww #wholesome#adorable</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/nczkNjX</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[charizardkitty]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Eclectic dump</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Zn6f8K7</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/kcldSTk.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/RHFb2Ju.jp